A 40-year-old man has been arrested following a shootout
with police at Kwahhoshi area in Babanango, KwaZulu-Natal, on Sunday. Provincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said
it is alleged that on Sunday, December 27, at 2.30 am, a taxi with 13
passengers was shot at by unknown suspects whilst travelling at Cacaneni area
in Ekombe. ALSO READ | Two suspects killed during shoot-out with police in Durban She said four people aged between 24 and 56 were declared
dead at the scene. One passenger was injured while others escaped unharmed.
Charges of murder and attempted murder were opened for investigation by Ekombe
SAPS. Mbele said on Sunday, the police followed up information
regarding the suspects involved and the suspect’s vehicle was spotted at Kwahhoshi
area in Babanango. When approached, Mbele said the police were met by a hail of
bullets and a shoot-out ensued. She said during the crossfire, the police
managed to arrest a 40-year-old man. He was found in illegal possession of a
firearm and ammunition. Mbele said police also seized the vehicle used by the
suspect. ALSO READ | Cop injured in New Germany shootout Police are still searching for the other two suspects who
managed to flee the scene. The suspect is appearing before the Babanango
Magistrates Court on Monday on charges of illegal possession of a firearm and
ammunition as well as murder and attempted murder. The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant
General Khombinkosi Jula praised the team for the speedy arrest of the murder
suspect. “I am confident that the remaining suspects will be caught soon,” he
said.